						               													<description>Flames of War: Cassino is about the Italian front from Januari till May 1944. It contains armylists, painting guides and background information about the battles that took place.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Armylists included in this book are:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Germans:&amp;#10;1. Fallschirmj&amp;auml;gerkompanie &amp;#10;44. 'Hoc und Deutschmeister' Infanteriedivision&amp;#10;90. 'Sardinien' Panzergrenadierdivision&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Allies:&amp;#10;French Expeditionary Force (FEC)&amp;#10;US 442nd Regimental Combat Team 'Nisei'&amp;#10;US 41st Cavalry Reconnaissance Squadron&amp;#10;British 4th and 8th Indian Infantry Divisions&amp;#10;British Ghurka assault troops&amp;#10;British 4th New Zealand Armoured Brigade&amp;#10;British 2nd New Zealand Infantry Division&amp;#10;British 28th New Zealand 'Maori' Batallion&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In addition to the army lists included, there is also a new escalation campaign system called &amp;quot;Infantry Aces&amp;quot; in which players have infantry units that gain experience from campaign battle to campaign battle, and each battle is fought in succession. &amp;#10;There are 3 different escalation routes, The Liri Valley, the town of Cassino, and through the mountains.Each contains 3 battles, of 500, then 700, then 900 points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To coincide with the release of this army book, new infantry miniatures are released that can be used by players as representatives of their &amp;quot;Infantry Aces&amp;quot; command teams.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
